Bug + constraints (SQLite + Drizzle better-sqlite3 migrator). Migration 0005 recreates `tasks` (DROP + rename). `task_events.task_id REFERENCES tasks(id) ON DELETE CASCADE` (keep the cascade). The connection (client.ts) is opened with `PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON`. Drizzle's migrator runs each migration file INSIDE a transaction, and SQLite treats `PRAGMA foreign_keys` as a NO-OP when issued inside a transaction — so the in-SQL `PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF` does nothing and the DROP cascades, wiping task_events.

CONSTRAINT ON THE FIX: do NOT edit the migration SQL and do NOT weaken the cascade. The fix must live in this function and must disable FK enforcement at the CONNECTION level (where there is no open transaction) before migrate() runs, then restore it. better-sqlite3 exposes `conn.pragma("foreign_keys = OFF")` and `conn.pragma("foreign_keys", { simple: true })`. The drizzle db wraps a better-sqlite3 connection `sqlite`.

