Reference — known pitfalls in this stack (consider which, if any, apply; rule each in or out against the evidence):
- An EventEmitter 'error' event with no listener crashes the process; try/catch around the emitting call does not catch it.
- `PRAGMA foreign_keys` is silently ignored (a no-op) when issued inside an open transaction.
- Drizzle's better-sqlite3 migrator executes each migration file inside a single transaction.
- A WAL checkpoint on close throws if the DB file was already unlinked.
- better-sqlite3 is fully synchronous; await/Promises do not apply to its calls.
- Native addons under worker_threads can segfault at process teardown.
- Grep/string-match audits over source also match occurrences inside comments and string literals.

